Date: 17/6/1943
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 4
Edition:
Quote: REHABILITATION .. Some 16,000 men had been demobilised in recent months, and only 25 of them had been placed on the land. Something should be done to hurry things along. New Zealand had not for many years had a Minister of Lands who understood land settlement, and possibly that was why there was not one word in the Budget concerning land settlement.
